  "created": "2025-10-13",
  "description": "The GAL gene regulatory system in yeast controls galactose metabolism through a sophisticated genetic switch involving three regulatory proteins: Gal4p (transcriptional activator), Gal80p (inhibitor), and Gal3p (inducer). This system demonstrates hierarchical gene regulation with glucose repression (catabolite repression) and galactose induction, operating through multiple logic gates to coordinate expression of GAL1, GAL7, GAL10, and other genes required for galactose utilization.",
